Suppose \(f\colon {\mathbb{R}} \to {\mathbb{R}}\) is a function and \(\lvert f(x) \rvert \leq \lvert x \rvert\)
for all \(x.\)  Then 
\(\displaystyle \lim_{x \to 0} f(x) = 0 . \)
$BR
END_TEXT
