$PAR
True or false:
Suppose
\(f\colon {\mathbb{R}} \to {\mathbb{R}}\)
and
\(g\colon {\mathbb{R}} \to {\mathbb{R}}\)
are functions and \(\lvert g(x) \rvert \leq \lvert f(x) \rvert \leq 2 \lvert g(x) \rvert\)
for all \(x.\)  Then 
\(\displaystyle \lim_{x \to 0} f(x) = 0 \)
if and only if
\(\displaystyle \lim_{x \to 0} g(x) = 0 . \)
$BR
END_TEXT
